descriptionHtml:
Description:
Completely replaces Skyrim's ugly lighting with ENBSeries's .319 lighting engine. Doesn't change any of the original atheistic or make any changes that would result in a change in gameplay, in fact improving upon it. This is done with little impact on performance at all whilst using the newest and best looking version of ENB

Compatibilty:
Compatible with any mod out there except for ones the interfere with ENBSeries (e.x. a different enb, enboost)

Reccomended Mods:
[url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/33582/?]Grass on Steriods[/url] For denser grass and better FPS
[url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/12525/?]Dynavision[/url] for dynamic no FPS loss depth of field
[url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/13049/?]Imaginator[/url] for customizing the look of your game

Pre-Install:
[b]Follow these steps for best optimization and performance[/b]
Make sure SKSE is installed, if not download and install [url=http://skse.silverlock.org/]here[/url]
Download and install SSME [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/50305/?]here[/url]
Download and Install TESV Acceleration layer [url=http://forums.bethsoft.com/topic/1321575-rel-tesv-acceleration-layer/]here[/url]
Download and run Ordenardor [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/12801/?]here[/url]

Installation:
(Part 1)
-Download the latest ENBSeries from [url=http://enbdev.com/mod_tesskyrim_v0319.htm]here[/url]
-Copy the contents into your Skyrim directory
(Part 2)
-Download this mod
-Copy contents into Skyrim directory
author: Paradoxical
